{"id":24850,"date":"2017-05-24T08:45:33","date_gmt":"2017-05-24T04:45:33","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=24850"},"modified":"2024-02-16T04:48:52","modified_gmt":"2024-02-16T00:48:52","slug":"salaf-fasting-remember-poor","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/05\/24\/salaf-fasting-remember-poor\/","title":{"rendered":"Salaf on Fasting: Remember the poor, starving while fasting"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Hassan ibn Ahmad reported: He asked the commander of the faithful Al-Ma&#8217;mun &#8216;Ali ibn Musa al-Rida, may Allah have mercy on him, \u201cIs there any benefit to fasting in the wisdom?\u201d Al-Ma&#8217;mun said, \u201cAllah Almighty knows what the impoverished endure of severe hunger, so He made the rich perform fasting that by necessity they might taste the flavor of hunger, such that they do not forget the severe hunger of the impoverished.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Tab\u1e63irah li-Ibn al-Jawz\u012b 2\/74<\/p>\n<p>Ibn Rajab reported: Some of the righteous predecessors were asked, \u201cWhy has fasting been instituted?\u201d They said, \u201cThat the rich will taste hunger and thus will not forget the hungry.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Lat\u0323a\u0304\u02bcif al-Ma\u02bba\u0304rif 1\/168<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u062d\u064e\u0633\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627\u0634\u0650\u0645\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0623\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0645\u064f\u0648\u0633\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0651\u0650\u0636\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0634\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0621\u064d \u0641\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u062f\u